<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_class_mim  Entity: exclusive_product_concept_feature_category  
   <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.exclusive_product_concept_feature_category"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.exclusive_product_concept_feature_category">
An <b>exclusive_product_concept_feature_category</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.product_concept_feature"/> in which the contained product_concept_feature instances describes mutually exclusive characteristics of a product. See ARM AM Product_class (1103) definition for <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Specification_category"/> for more information.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_class_mim  Entity: inclusion_product_concept_feature  
   <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.inclusion_product_concept_feature"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.inclusion_product_concept_feature">
An <b>inclusion_product_concept_feature</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.conditional_concept_feature"/> that is the representation of the statement that the application of a <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.product_concept_feature"/> or of a <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.conditional_concept_feature"/> implies the inclusion of an additional <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.product_concept_feature"/> or <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.conditional_concept_feature"/>. 
See ARM AM Product_class (1103) definition for <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Specification_inclusion"/> for more information.
 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_class_mim  Entity: inclusion_product_concept_feature  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.inclusion_product_concept_feature.wr:WR1"/>
	   ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.inclusion_product_concept_feature.wr:WR1">
An <b>inclusion_product_concept_feature</b> shall not be of type <b>package_product_concept_feature</b>. 

</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_class_mim  Entity: inclusion_product_concept_feature  Where: WR2 
   <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.inclusion_product_concept_feature.wr:WR2"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.inclusion_product_concept_feature.wr:WR2">
An <b>inclusion_product_concept_feature</b> shall not be referenced as relating_product_concept_feature nor as related_product_concept_feature by <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.concept_feature_relationship_with_condition"/> instances. 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_class_mim  Entity: inclusion_product_concept_feature  Where: WR3 
   <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.inclusion_product_concept_feature.wr:WR3"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.inclusion_product_concept_feature.wr:WR3">
An <b>inclusion_product_concept_feature</b> shall reference as condition a <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.concept_feature_relationship_with_condition"/> which references a concept_feature_operator with a name of 'implication'. 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_class_mim  Entity: package_product_concept_feature  
   <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.package_product_concept_feature"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.package_product_concept_feature">
A <b>package_product_concept_feature</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.product_concept_feature"/> that is a combination of product_concept_features that shall be offered to the market as a set.
See ARM AM Product_class (1103) definition for <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Specification"/> for more information.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_class_mim  Entity: package_product_concept_feature  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.package_product_concept_feature.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.package_product_concept_feature.wr:WR1">
A <b>package_product_concept_feature</b> shall not be of type <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.conditional_concept_feature"/>. 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_class_mim  Entity: package_product_concept_feature  Where: WR2 
   <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.package_product_concept_feature.wr:WR2"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.package_product_concept_feature.wr:WR2">
A <b>package_product_concept_feature</b> shall be referenced as relating_product_concept_feature by at least one <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.concept_feature_relationship_with_condition"/> which is referenced as condition by a <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.conditional_concept_feature"/> of type <b>inclusion_product_concept_feature</b>. 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_class_mim  Entity: product_class  
   <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.product_class"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.product_class">
A <b>product_class</b> is a type of product_concept and characterized_object that is the identification of a set of similar products to be offered to the market.
See ARM AM Product_class (1103) definition for <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Product_class"/> for more information.
 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_class_mim  Entity: product_concept_feature_category  
   <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.product_concept_feature_category"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.product_concept_feature_category">
A <b>product_concept_feature_category</b> is a type of group that specifies a set of similar <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.product_concept_feature"/> instances.
See ARM AM Product_class (1103) definition for <express_ref linkend="product_class:arm:Product_class_arm.Specification_category"/> for more information.
 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_class_mim  Entity: product_concept_feature_category  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.product_concept_feature_category.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.product_concept_feature_category.wr:WR1">
A <b>product_concept_feature_category</b> shall only be referenced as assigned_group by 
<express_ref linkend="group:mim:Group_mim.applied_group_assignment"/>
instances which reference as role an object_role with a name of 'specification category member' and which only contain product_concept_features in their set of items which are not of type conditional_concept_feature</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_class_mim  Entity: product_concept_feature_category_usage  
   <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.product_concept_feature_category_usage"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.product_concept_feature_category_usage">
A <b>product_concept_feature_category_usage</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="management_resources_schema:ir_express:management_resources_schema.group_assignment"/> that is the assignment of a <b>product_concept_feature_category</b> to a <b>product_class</b>. Additionally this assignment specifies if the usage of one or more product_concept_features belonging to this <b>product_concept_feature_category</b> is mandatory or optional for all products of that <b>product_class</b>. 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_class_mim  Entity: product_concept_feature_category_usage  Attribute: assigned_group 
   <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.product_concept_feature_category_usage.assigned_group"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.product_concept_feature_category_usage.assigned_group">
The attribute <b>assigned_group</b> of <b>product_concept_feature_category_usage</b> shall be of type <b>product_concept_feature_category</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_class_mim  Entity: product_concept_feature_category_usage  Attribute: items 
   <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.product_concept_feature_category_usage.items"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.product_concept_feature_category_usage.items">
Items is the set of items to which the <b>product_concept_feature_category</b> is assigned.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_class_mim  Entity: product_concept_feature_category_usage  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.product_concept_feature_category_usage.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.product_concept_feature_category_usage.wr:WR1">
The <b>product_concept_feature_category_usage</b> shall have as role an object_role with a name of 'mandatory category usage' or 'optional category usage'. 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_class_mim  Rule: restrict_concept_feature_operator 
   <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.restrict_concept_feature_operator"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.restrict_concept_feature_operator">
The <b>restrict_concept_feature_operator</b> rule restricts the name and usage of a <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.concept_feature_operator"/>. 
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.restrict_concept_feature_operator.wr:WR1">
Each instance of <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.concept_feature_operator"/> shall have a name of 'and', 'or', 'oneof, 'not', or 'implication'. 
 </ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.restrict_concept_feature_operator.wr:WR2">
If the <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.concept_feature_operator"/> has a name of 'implication', it shall only be referenced as conditional_operator by <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.concept_feature_relationship_with_condition"/> instances which are referenced as the condition by conditional_concept_features which are of type <b>inclusion_product_concept_feature</b>. 
 </ext_description>
 <ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.restrict_concept_feature_operator.wr:WR3">
If the <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.concept_feature_operator"/> has a name of 'not'  it shall only be referenced as conditional_operator by <express_ref linkend="product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.concept_feature_relationship_with_condition"/> instances which are referenced as the condition.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_class_mim  Rule: restrict_group_relationship_for_specification_category 
   <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.restrict_group_relationship_for_specification_category"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.restrict_group_relationship_for_specification_category">
The <b>restrict_group_relationship_for_specification_category</b> rule ensures the correct correlation between the name of a <express_ref linkend="group_schema:ir_express:group_schema.group_relationship"/> and the related groups of type <b>product_concept_feature_category</b>. 
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend
="Product_class_mim.restrict_group_relationship_for_specification_category.wr:WR1">
If the <express_ref linkend="group_schema:ir_express:group_schema.group_relationship"/> has a name of 'specification category hierarchy', the related_group and the relating_group shall be of type <b>product_concept_feature_category</b>. 
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_class_mim  Rule: product_concept_feature_requires_category 
   <express_ref linkend="product_class:mim:Product_class_mim.product_concept_feature_requires_category"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.product_concept_feature_requires_category">
The <b>product_concept_feature_requires_category</b> rule specifies that each instance of 
<express_ref linkend=
"product_concept_schema:ir_express:product_concept_schema.product_concept_feature"/>
is contained in the set of items of exactly one 
<express_ref linkend="group:mim:Group_mim.applied_group_assignment"/> 
which has as the role an object_role with a name of 'specification category member' and which references as the assigned_group a product_concept_feature_category. This rule enforces the requirement for every Specification to have one Specification_category. 
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Product_class_mim.product_concept_feature_requires_category.wr:WR1">
Each instance of <b>product_concept_feature</b> 
is contained in the set of items of exactly one 
<express_ref linkend="group:mim:Group_mim.applied_group_assignment"/>
which has as the role an object_role with a name of 'specification category member' 
and which references as the assigned_group a <b>product_concept_feature_category</b>. 
 </ext_description>
 </ext_descriptions>
